messages.content: Which agent should I talk to about building and housing I have some code questions and I want to tear down a building downtown

For questions related to building and housing code, you should contact the **Division of Code Enforcement** within the Cleveland Department of Building & Housing. They are responsible for enforcing the housing code and property maintenance code.

If your inquiry involves demolishing a building downtown, you should reach out to the **Building & Housing Director** or the **Chief Housing Official**, as they oversee the city's demolition program. They can provide guidance on the necessary steps and requirements for demolition.

For specific contact details, you can refer to the Cleveland Department of Building & Housing's contact directory or call their main office for assistance.
